## Functional Descriptions:
   - **TaELF3-1DL**, a homolog of ELF3, is associated with heading date in bread wheat.
   - **TaELF3-1DL**b is associated with early HD. Thus, the functional marker can be used in wheat breeding programs.
   - A quantitative trait locus (QTL) for heading date (HD) co-segregating with **TaELF3-1DL** explained 7.7â€“20.6% of the phenotypic variance in a RIL mapping population derived from the Gaocheng 8901/Zhoumai 16 cross genotyped using the wheat 90K iSelect assay.
   - Validate function of the **TaELF3** gene on flowering by linkage mapping.
